&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;text-decoration: underline;&quot;&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;About Us&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;Founded in 1967, QLS seeks equal access to justice for all low-income residents of Queens through a range of legal advocacy,&amp;nbsp;education&amp;nbsp;and community partnerships. We provide free legal counseling, representation and referrals in civil matters involving fundamental needs&amp;nbsp;including housing, public and disability benefits, domestic violence prevention, consumer and homeowner protections, access to education and employment rights to eligible low-income individuals and families. We work with our clients and partners to&amp;nbsp;identify&amp;nbsp;and address root causes for systemic inequalities in Queens and throughout New York City. We provide civil legal services at our office in Jamaica and via outreach in the Queens community. We are part of Legal Services NYC, the largest free civil legal services provider in the United States.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span data-contrast=&quot;auto&quot;&gt;DVFLAP is an interdisciplinary team of attorney and social workers whose mission is to provide holistic and culturally competent services to enable victims of intimate partner violence&amp;nbsp;to live free of abuse and violence. Our attorneys provide direct legal representation to domestic violence survivors for family legal matters in Family Court, Supreme&amp;nbsp;Court&amp;nbsp;and in the IDV Part.&amp;nbsp;DVFLAP staff conduct borough-wide outreach and community education workshops related to family law and domestic violence.&amp;nbsp;DVFLAP staff are actively involved in community task forces and working groups and&amp;nbsp;advocate on&amp;nbsp;systemic and macro levels for policy changes to advance economic, racial and gender justice for survivors of intimate partner violence.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span data-ccp-props=&quot;{}&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
